    This manual describes version &appversion; of &appname;.



	    Feedback


              To send feedback, follow the directions in the Feedback Page.






MateDialog is a rewrite of gdialog, the MATE port of dialog which allows you to 
                  display dialog boxes from the commandline and shell scripts.

sect1.para:
The following example script shows how to create a calendar dialog:
#!/bin/sh
if matedialog --calendar \ --title="Select a Date" \ --text="Click on a date to select that date." \ --day=10 --month=8 --year=2004 then echo $? else echo "No date selected" fi

The following example script shows how to create a file selection dialog:


  #!/bin/sh

  FILE=`matedialog --file-selection --title="Select a File"`

  case $? in
           0)
                  echo "\"$FILE\" selected.";;
           1)
                  echo "No file selected.";;
          -1)
                  echo "No file selected.";;
  esac

The following example script shows how to create a notification icon:
#!/bin/sh
matedialog --notification\ --window-icon="info" \ --text="There are system updates necessary!"

The following example script shows how to create a list dialog:
#!/bin/sh
matedialog --list \ --title="Choose the Bugs You Wish to View" \ --column="Bug Number" --column="Severity" --column="Description" \ 992383 Normal "GtkTreeView crashes on multiple selections" \ 293823 High "MATE Dictionary does not handle proxy" \ 393823 Critical "Menu editing does not work in MATE 2.0"

sect2.para:
The following example script shows how to create an error dialog:
#!/bin/bash
matedialog --error \ --text="Could not find /var/log/syslog."

The following example script shows how to create an information dialog:
#!/bin/bash
matedialog --info \ --text="Merge complete. Updated 3 of 10 files."

The following example script shows how to create a question dialog:
#!/bin/bash
matedialog --question \ --text="Are you sure you wish to proceed?"

The following example script shows how to create a warning dialog:
#!/bin/bash
matedialog --warning \ --text="Disconnect the power cable to avoid electrical shock."

sect1.para:
The following example script shows how to create a progress dialog:
#!/bin/sh ( echo "10" ; sleep 1 echo "# Updating mail logs" ; sleep 1 echo "20" ; sleep 1 echo "# Resetting cron jobs" ; sleep 1 echo "50" ; sleep 1 echo "This line will just be ignored" ; sleep 1 echo "75" ; sleep 1 echo "# Rebooting system" ; sleep 1 echo "100" ; sleep 1 ) | matedialog --progress \ --title="Update System Logs" \ --text="Scanning mail logs..." \ --percentage=0
if [ "$?" = -1 ] ; then matedialog --error \ --text="Update canceled." fi

The following example script shows how to create a text entry dialog:
#!/bin/sh
if matedialog --entry \ --title="Add an Entry" \ --text="Enter your _password:" \ --entry-text "password" \ --hide-text then echo $? else echo "No password entered" fi
